result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher M. White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher M. White is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher M. White was found guilty of Sex Offender - Fail/Update Information, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(4)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:14 Defendant Christopher M. White in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 14CM125 heard at this time. Froelich: guilty Ct#1 14CF134 1 year probation. Dismiss Ct#2. Guilty to Ct#1 in 14CM125 with minumum fine and dismiss Ct#2. Nelson and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#1 in 14CF134 and Ct#1 in 14CM125; Nelson stipulates to a factual basis for conviction.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#1 in 14CF134 and Ct#1 in 14CM125. Dismisses Ct#2 in 14CF134 and 14CM125. Froelich and Nelson address sentencing.  Court: S/W 1 year probation on 14CF134, conditions: comply with registration requirements, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.  Court: fine in the amount of $265.60 in 14CM125; gives 6 months.   Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea/sentencing hearing at 02-23-2015 11:00 am.  Personal service to parties on 01/20/15
Case has been reset for a couple of weeks out.
